    "created_at": "2013-06-03T18:44:06Z",
    "updated_at": "2013-06-03T18:44:06Z",
    "body": "@nikomatsakis: Yeah, they added `nullptr` only because using a zero constant often calls an overload you didn't expect it to without even warning about ambiguity. C++ defines `NULL` as `0` instead of `(void *)0` because the latter would then require casts to the specific pointer type.\n\nRust now treats casts to and from a raw pointer as a safe operation, so the original bug here is fixed. I'm going to close this and we can open another one if there are any lingering issues.\n",
